## 4. Technical Specification

### 4.1 Survivor Transition Function
The core function models the breakout from fixed-point density:

$$
T_{\text{survive}}(x) = x + 1
\quad\text{when}\quad x = 666
$$

### 4.2 Resilience Gradient
The resilience of the system is symbolized by the minimal required upward movement:

$$
R = \frac{667 - 666}{666} = \frac{1}{666}
$$
This represents that the **smallest possible upward movement is enough** to exit the pressure.

